{{Infobox artist | name = Ivan Grigorievich Savenko | image = Savenko-Ivan-Grigorievich-savenko bw.jpg | imagesize = 200px | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = January 17, 1924 | birth_place = [[Bakhmach Raion|Varvarovka]], [[Chernihiv Oblast|Chernigov Province]], [[Ukraine SSR|Ukraine]], USSR | death_date = December 17, 1987 | death_place = [[Leningrad]], [[USSR]] | field = [[Painting]] | citizenship = [[USSR]] | nationality = | training = [[Repin Institute of Arts]] | movement = [[Realism (visual art)|Realism]] | works = | patrons = | awards = [[Honored Artist of the RSFSR]] }}
'''Ivan Grigorievich Savenko''' ({{lang-ru|Ива́н Григо́рьевич Саве́нко}}; January 17, 1924, [[Bakhmach Raion|Varvarovka]], [[Chernihiv Oblast|Chernigov Province]], [[Ukrainian SSR]], USSR &ndash; 1987, [[Leningrad]], USSR) was a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[Russians|Russian]] - [[Ukrainians|Ukrainian]] painter, [[Honored Artist of the RSFSR]], lived and worked in [[Leningrad]], regarded as one of representatives of the [[Leningrad School of Painting|Leningrad school of painting]],<ref>''Sergei V. Ivanov. Unknown Socialist Realism. The Leningrad School.''- Saint Petersburg: NP-Print Edition, 2007. – pp.18, 20, 368, 388-391, 393-397, 399-401, 403-406, 445.</ref> most famous for his landscape paintings.
== Biography ==
Ivan Savenko was born January 17, 1924, in [[Bakhmach Raion|Varvarovka]] village, [[Chernihiv Oblast|Chernigov Province]], [[Ukraine SSR|Ukraine]], USSR. He was a veteran of World War II, was wounded and lost his right hand, he had many military orders.
In 1950, Savenko graduated from Kiev Art Institute in Grigory Svetlitsky personal Art Studio.
In 1950–1954, Savenko studied as post-graduate student in [[Repin Institute of Arts|Ilya Repin Institute]] in [[Aleksandr Gerasimov (painter)|Aleksandr Gerasimov]] Art studio. Master of Art-criticism (1954). [[Honored Artist of the RSFSR|Honored Artist of the Russian Federation]] (1975).
Since 1950, Savenko has participated in Art Exhibitions. He painted landscapes, portraits, genre scenes, sketchs from the life. Personal Exhibition in Moscow (1990).
Savenko was a member of [[Leningrad Union of Artists]] since 1952.<ref>''Directory of members of the Leningrad branch of Union of Artists of Russian Federation.'' - Leningrad: Khudozhnik RSFSR, 1987. - p. 114.</ref>
Savenko died on December 17, 1987, in Leningrad. His paintings reside in [[Russian Museum|State Russian Museum]], [[Tretyakov Gallery|State Tretyakov Gallery]], in Art museums and private collections in Russia, France, Ukraine, Germany, Japan, Italy, England, and throughout the world.{{citation needed|date=November 2010}}
